wp kses check attr val "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
======================================================================

NAME
----

wp kses check attr val - Performs different checks for attribute values.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Performs different checks for attribute values.

The currently implemented checks are '`maxlen`', '`minlen`', '`maxval`',
'`minval`' and '`valueless`' with even more checks to come soon.

USAGE
-----

` <?php wp_kses_check_attr_val( $value, $vless, $checkname, $checkvalue ) ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$value` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Attribute value
    Default: *None*

 `$vless` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Whether the value is valueless or not. Use '`y`' or
    '`n`'
    Default: *None*

 `$checkname` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) What `$checkvalue` is checking for.
    Default: *None*

 `$checkvalue` 
:   ([*mixed*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Mixed "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) What constraint the value should pass
    Default: *None*

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 (boolean) 
:   Whether check passes (true) or not (false)

EXAMPLES
--------

NOTES
-----

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: 1.0.0

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`wp_kses_check_attr_val()` is located in `wp-includes/kses.php`.

